<div class="about-me py-5">
  <h1 class="mb-4 fw-bold">About Me</h1>

  <!-- Portrait: floats right on lg+, stacks above text on smaller screens -->
  <img
    src="/images/cycling_photo.jpg"
    alt="Idir Belkacem portrait"
    class="img-fluid rounded-3 shadow-sm mb-3 ms-4 float-end"
    style="width: 420px; max-width: 55%;"
    loading="lazy"
  />


  <p>
    Hi, I’m <strong>Idir</strong>, a junior C#/.NET software developer focused on practical business software and applications that support real workflows.
  </p>

  <p>
    I enjoy building software that helps people organise tasks, reduce manual work, and make information easier to use. My background combines a Master’s in Computer Science, over one year of commercial software-development experience, and practical work on digitisation, workflow, API, database, and full-stack application projects.
  </p>

  <p>
What matters to me is not only writing code, but understanding the problem behind it. I like working step by step, clarifying requirements, improving existing systems, documenting decisions, and building software that remains useful and maintainable.
  </p>

  <p class="mt-4">
Outside of work, I’m family-oriented and community-minded. I enjoy cooking, cycling, walks, and spending time with my wife and children. I also speak English, French, Arabic, Kabyle/Tamazight, and German at B2 level, which helps me connect with people from different backgrounds.
  </p>

  <p>
I’m currently growing further in C#/.NET, backend and full-stack development, and I’m especially interested in software that supports real business, operational, or technical processes.
  </p>

  <a href="/#contact" class="call-for-action fw-semibold">
    Let’s connect and explore what we can build together!
  </a>
